-- Gujarat Seeks Annual Contract for 2.5 Million Tons on Steam Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2013-09-05T09:45:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-05/gujarat-seeks-annual-contract-for-2-5-million-tons-on-steam-coal.html
Gujarat State Electricity Corp. is
seeking 2.5 million metric tons of imported thermal coal
annually for five years for its Sikka power plant.  The state-owned utility in western  India  is seeking power-plant coal of 5,500 kilocalories per kilogram with moisture of
18 percent, ash of 8 percent and sulfur of 0.6 percent,
according to the tender  document  on its website.  The company expects delivery starting April 2014 at Dahej,
Magdalla, Bedi, Navlakhi, Pipavav, Kandla or Mundra, the
document said. The tender closes Sept. 24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
